               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-129" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-129" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-129" type="surname" value="ASHPLANT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-129" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM ASHPLANT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a carpenter. On the 1st of June, I was working at a building in Castle-street, Holborn—I left my tools on the second floor—there was a hoard ten feet high round the building—in the morning when I came to work I missed them—about half-fast ten o'clock the same morning the prisoner was coming down Castle-street very much intoxicated—he fell down by the building, and the square fell out of his pocket—the policeman was lifting him up, and I found my saw in hit coat pocket—he had my partner's apron on, and he threw a gouge out of his pocket—a handkerchief was found in his hat—all these tools are mine—the prisoner is a perfect stranger.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-130" type="witnessName">
